Cabling Overview
	Issues Affecting Electrical Cabling
		EMI - Electromagnetic Interference
		Crosstalk - Signals "bleeding" from one cable to another adjacent cable [[img images/crosstalk.gif]]
	Types
		Coax
		Twisted Pair
		Fiber-Optic
---------------------------------
Coax
	Signal wire is wrapped in braided shield to protect from EMI [[img images/coax.jpg]]
	Old LAN versions utilizes BNC Connectors [[img http://www.eeherald.com/images/10base5_bnc_connector_aiu_dix.jpg]]
	Using cable with correct impedance (measured in ohms) is important
	RG Ratings (lower the number, bigger the cable)
		RG-6 (Cable TV, 75ohm)
		RG-58 (old LANS, 50 ohm)
		RG-59 (AV connections, 75 ohm)
	No longer common for LANS
---------------------------------
Twisted Pair
	Wire pairs are twisted to cancel out EMI [[img http://www.networkcablinglosangeles.com/wp-content/themes/networkcablinglosangeles/images/unshielded_cable.jpg]]
	Shielded (STP) and Unshielded (UTP) are available
	Connectors
		RJ11 - Phone [[img http://us.123rf.com/400wm/400/400/ra3rn/ra3rn1106/ra3rn110600012/9866377-cable-network-connection-isolated-on-a-white-background-an-ethernet-rj45-cable.jpg]]
		RJ45 - Networking [[img http://www.taiko-net.com.tr/TRImage/category%205%20cable-1.gif]]
	Category Ratings
		CAT 3 - Phone Grade
		CAT 5 - 100 Mbps
		CAT 5e - 1000 Mbps (1Gbps)
		CAT 6 - 10 Gpbs
	Fire Ratings
		pvc 
		[[Plenum!http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plenum_cable]]
